<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1426,1972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,348,1546,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Recognition</emphasis>
. This species is distinguished by the following features: head, thorax and abdomen mostly shiny, male genitalia small, not expanded laterally beyond abdomen, left surstylus long and strongly arched, and hypoproct with long hook-like projection, arching to left side.
</paragraph>
